.TH "FILES" "1" "2026\-04\-11" "Winix" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
files \- find files by name, size, date, type, and content
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]files\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[I]paths\f[R]\&...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Walks one or more directories (default: \f[B].\f[R] ) and prints
matching file paths to stdout, one per line.
Supports glob and regex name matching, type filtering, size and date
ranges, text/binary detection, and structured output.
.PP
Results are printed to stdout; the \f[B]\(enjson\f[R] envelope is also
emitted to stdout (suite convention) and is structured so it composes
cleanly with \f[B]jq\f[R].
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]\-g\f[R], \f[B]\(englob\f[R] \f[I]PATTERN\f[R]
Match filenames against a glob pattern (repeatable).
.TP
\f[B]\-e\f[R], \f[B]\(enregex\f[R] \f[I]PATTERN\f[R]
Match filenames against a regex (repeatable).
.TP
\f[B]\(enext\f[R] \f[I]EXT\f[R]
Match file extension, e.g.\ \f[B]cs\f[R], \f[B]log\f[R] (repeatable).
.TP
\f[B]\-t\f[R], \f[B]\(entype\f[R] \f[I]TYPE\f[R]
Filter by type: \f[B]f\f[R] (file), \f[B]d\f[R] (directory), \f[B]l\f[R]
(symlink).
.TP
\f[B]\(entext\f[R]
Only text files.
.TP
\f[B]\(enbinary\f[R]
Only binary files.
.TP
\f[B]\(enmin\-size\f[R] \f[I]SIZE\f[R]
Minimum file size (e.g.\ \f[B]100k\f[R], \f[B]10M\f[R], \f[B]1G\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]\(enmax\-size\f[R] \f[I]SIZE\f[R]
